You can explore insights for any model to which you have access. An insight is a statistically significant finding in your data.

Navigate Data Insights
Learn about the data insights interface and how to interact with it.
Explore Insights for a Variable
Explore how an explanatory variable is related to your model’s goal.
Compare Subgroups with the Global Average
Explore how a subgroup (category or bucket) relates to a variable’s global average.

Compare Subgroups
Compare subgroups (categories or buckets) to learn how they relate to your model’s goal. For example, you can compare the sales performance between two different territories (such as “North America” and “Europe”). Einstein Discovery displays a waterfall chart to help you visualize the comparison between territories.

Explore Predictions and Improvements
Explore predicted outcomes and suggested ways to improve those predicted outcomes.

Explore Insights for Multiclass Outcomes
Learn what Einstein Discovery insights can tell you about your multiclass classification solution.
Explore Bias in Multiclass Outcomes
Bias detection in multiclass models alerts you of the presence of bias so you can mitigate its distorting effects in your analysis.
Explore Predictions for Multiclass Outcomes
Explore predicted outcomes for multiclass models.

Bookmark an Insight in a Model
Bookmarking an insight allows you to export it to a Quip document. 

Get Descriptive and Diagnostic Insights Programmatically
Use Einstein Discovery's Insights API to embed insights from your model into any website, application, or dashboard.
title: Exploring Data Insights with Einstein Discovery
